15/02/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- Director of National Intelligence John Negroponte praised Bulgaria's participation in the fight against terrorism, describing Sofia as a strategic partner in this field.
Negroponte met on Tuesday (14 February) with visiting Bulgarian Interior Minister Rumen Petkov.
They discussed bilateral and regional co-operation, security issues and next month's conference of Southeast European countries' interior ministers in Sofia.
In other news, Bulgarian Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev is paying a daylong visit to neighbouring Romania.
He will meet with counterpart Calin Popescu Tariceanu and parliamentary leaders.
(Sega, 24 Chasa - 15/02/06;
Bulgarian Government Web site, bTV, Mediapool - 14/02/06)
